<TEXT>
<P>
   EDITORS:
</P>
<P>
   Esther Dyson's latest ``Release 3.0'' column followed her visit
to the recent summit of business and political leaders at Davos. In
the column she contrasted the ``Internet-ready'' culture of the
U.S. with the much more regulated political cultures of Europe and
Asia.
</P>
<P>
   It certainly resonated with new international subscribers
including the South China Morning Post (Hong Kong), El Pais
(Madrid) and Yomiuri Shimbun (Tokyo).
</P>
<P>
   Domestically, new additions to the subscriber list include the
Seattle Post-Inteligencer, Orange County Register, San Francisco
Examiner, Rocky Mountain News, Los Angeles Times and the St. Paul
Pioneer-Press.
</P>
<P>
   For a look at Esther's next column (due to be transmitted next
Wednesday), or to obtain more information about Esther, call Bob
Farnell at 1-800-535-4425, or e-mail him at
farnellb(at)nytimes.com.)
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times Syndicate
</P>
