<SLUG> BC-BESTSELLERS-PAPER-L-$ADV20-2NDTAKE-NYT </SLUG>
  
 UNDATED: Virginia Woolf.  
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; NONFICTION &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ANGELA'S ASHES, by Frank McCourt. (Touchstone/S&AMP;S, ......... 1
... 37
</P>
<P>
   $14 and $7.99.) An Irish-American writer recalls his
</P>
<P>
   childhood amid the miseries of Limerick.
</P>
<P>
   THE SEAT OF THE SOUL, by Gary Zukav. (Fireside/S&AMP;S, ........ 2
... 66
</P>
<P>
   $12.) How daily activities can be enhanced by feelings
</P>
<P>
   of meaning and purpose. (b)
</P>
<P>
   GIRL, INTERRUPTED, by Susanna Kaysen. (Vintage, $12.) ...... 3
... 30
</P>
<P>
   A memoir of mental illness.
</P>
<P>
   A CHILD CALLED ``IT,'' by Dave Pelzer. (Health ............. 4
... 92
</P>
<P>
   Communications, $9.95.) The autobiography of a man
</P>
<P>
   who survived his mother's abuse. (b)
</P>
<P>
   THE PERFECT STORM, by Sebastian Junger. .................... 5
... 88
