<P>
   CONGRESS-OUTLOOK (Washington) _ A month into this
campaign-compressed congressional year, it's hard to tell which
Congress will emerge: the incrementally productive one that is
working with the White House to pass a key China trade bill and
repeal limits on Social Security earnings, or the do-nothing one
that's fighting Bill Clinton on taxes, debt relief and his spending
plans. An early handicapping of where we are and where we might go.
By Eric Schmitt. (1100 words)
</P>
<P>
   MILITARY-ANTHRAX (Washington) _ Rep. Shays and the House
Government Oversight Committee release report critical of the
Defense Department program to innoculate American troops for
anthrax. By Steven Lee Myers.
</P>
