   &UR; INTERNATIONAL &LR;  (``i'' code)
</P>
<P>
   IRAN-ELECT (Tehran) _ Iran votes Friday in nationwide
parliamentary election, a crucial showdown between reformers and
conservative clerics. By Susan Sachs.
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-BANK (Moscow) _ Who owns, who uses, and what are the
Kremlin ties, if any, to the Russian banks named in the guilty plea
in the Bank of New York case. By Celestine Bohlen.
</P>
<P>
   LEBANON-U.S. (Beirut) _ About 2,000 protesters try to storm the
U.S. Embassy here, unhappy with what they say is U.S. support for
Israeli air strikes in Lebanon. Developing. By John F. Burns.
</P>
<P>
   U.N.-TUVALU (United Nations) _ Tuvalu _ a country of nine
islands whose name means ``eight islands'' (the ninth was inhabited
more recently) _ becomes the 189th member of the United Nations. By
Barbara Crossette.
</P>
<P>
   With graphic.
</P>
