says Cheryl Mendelson, the very real know-how required for
housekeeping has been largely lost, like a language nobody wrote
down. So she herself wrote it down. By Carol Stocker. 1770 words.
</P>
<P>
   HOME-FIREPLACES (Undated) _ Fireplaces will continue to be the
focal point in a room, but they'll wear different clothes and
operate from a different source. By Patti Doten. (2 takes) PHOTO
</P>
<P>
   CHILDCARE-COLUMN (Undated) _ Just because we are busy married
people with children does not mean we are doomed to a romance-free
marriage that grows more distant or eventually fails. By Barbara
Meltz. 1700 words.
</P>
