<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-POLITICS-ADVISORY-NYT </SLUG>
  
 (Updates from AM-BUDGET, adding GORE-LABOR.)  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; POLITICS &LR;  (``p'' code)
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times plans three pages of stories, photos and
graphics on the presidential campaign:
</P>
<P>
   SC-VOICES (Dateline to kum, S.C.) _ South Carolina voters speak
ahead of Saturday's vote. A Ledeall by By R.W. Apple Jr.
</P>
<P>
   Plus these separates, at 750 words each:
</P>
<P>
   _ SC-VOICES-CONSERVATIVES _ Conservative Republicans. By Jim
Yardley.
</P>
<P>
   _ SC-VOICES-LOWCOUNTRY _ Low Country Republicans. By Gustav
Niehuhr.
