   TORNADOES-MEMORIAL _ A memorial service will be held Thursday
for fatalities in this week's tornadoes. (Chapman, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   GUNS-GEORGIA _ ATLANTA _ Gov. Roy Barnes calls Thursday news
conference to announce legislation to strengthen Georgia's gun
laws. (Pruitt, Atlanta Journal-Costitution).
</P>
<P>
   GA-FLA-WATERWARS _ Breaking a long-held silence on Georgia's
water war with Florida and Alabama, outgoing Atlanta Regional
Commission Director Harry West warns that the current direction of
the negotiations means ``perpetual drought will become the normal
operating procedure for metropolitan Atlanta.'' In a letter to
Harold Reheis and Bob Kerr, Georgia's chief negotiators, West says
the agreement on the table is one sided - ``Florida gets all of the
guarantees; Georgia gets none.'' Negotiators for the three states
have until May 1 to reach an agreement, but West's letter could
throw a monkey wrench in the proceedings. (Seabrook, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   ALA-POKER _ In rural Macon County, just east of Montgomery,
VictoryLand dog track is the No. 1 local industry. It provides 400
jobs to cashiers, janitors and dog grooms. At one time, it was the
top dog track in the nation. Then came the casinos in Mississippi,
and there went the business. To save the track, two state
legislators want the people of their county to have the chance to
authorize video gambling at the track. ``I'd vote for it. If we had
it at the track, then we wouldn't have to go to Mississippi, would
we?'' said Virginia Fannin, owner of the Fannin Grocery just down
the road on U.S. 80. The bill is scheduled for a public debate the
week of Feb. 7. (Manuel, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). WITH PHOTO
(Mugshot of Ala. state Rep. Johnny Ford). MOVED
</P>
<P>
   POLITICS
</P>
<P>
   BUSH _ George W. Bush sends in his own proxy to Michigan and
it's someone with a little higher profile than Mike DeWine _ Bush's
dad. (Hershey, Dayton Daily News)
</P>
<P>
   MCCAIN-VOICES _ A look at the McCain surge from various sites
around the country. (Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   XTIANVOTE _ Pat Robertson and other Christian leaders have
strongly attacked John McCain and urged their followers to support
Bush. But are the followers following? (Burritt, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 25.
</P>
<P>
   GOP-ISSUES _ They don't walk alike. They don't talk alike. But a
close look at the issues shows that for all their style difference,
Gov. George W. Bush and Arizona Sen. John McCain think pretty much
alike. A look behind style at the substance. (Heath, Austin
American-Statesman). 30.
</P>
<P>
   POL-TICKER _ A brief roundup of the day's campaign events,
pulled from Cox staff and wire reports. (Cox News Service) ETA: 6
p.m.
</P>
<P>
   FAMILY-CANDIDATES _The staffs of every major presidential
candidate have called 2-year-old Kaitlynn Bogan's parents in West
Alexandria after the family told Vice President Al Gore last week
about its battle over health insurance, Kaitlynn's mother said.
(Lamb, Dayton Daily News).
</P>
