   REPUBS-SC (Myrtle Beach, S.C.) _ A ledeall: With only two days
to go before a Republican primary that's too close to call, Gov.
George W. Bush and Sen. John McCain raced across South Carolina
Thursday, with Bush continuing his aggressive attacks on his
opponent and McCain seeking as large a turnout as possible. By
Alison Mitchell and Frank Bruni.
