   MOUNTAIN-SUICIDE (East Corinth, Vt.) _ Guy Waterman knew more
about the White Mountains than just about anyone, and apparently
had more demons than even his good friends realized. Earlier this
month, the noted wilderness author, presidential speechwriter and
accomplished hiker left a detailed note in his Vermont home,
climbed to the summit of Mount Lafayette, and deliberately froze to
death. By David Arnold. 1300 words.
