   FED-GREENSPAN-REACT (Undated) _ When Alan Greenspan speaks, the
old economy trembles. But the new one thinks it is impervious to
higher interest rates, and shrugs off warnings from the Fed
chairman. That has been the pattern since the Fed began to raise
interest rates last summer, and it continued Thursday. Greenspan's
stark warnings that short-term interest rates would continue to
rise had only a brief impact on the Nasdaq composite index, which
is dominated by high-technology companies that are benefiting from
the digital revolution. By Floyd Norris. (Explainer with
FED-GREENSPAN)
</P>
