<P>
   MICROSOFT-WINDOWS (Seattle) _ Microsoft partied as it unveiled
its new Windows 2000 operating system in San Francisco, accompanied
by rock stars and an actor, cheering fans and a 40-foot high laptop
with keys the size of stepping stones. But chairman Bill Gates only
rarely cracked a smile as the hoopla reached its pitch, a telling
reminder that this is the product upon which the Redmond company
has risked its future.
</P>
