administrators to reprimand Gates for using university resources
for personal profit. A quarter century after the billionaire's
pioneering days at Harvard, a mushrooming number of student-founded
computer companies on campus is forcing the university to
reconsider its policy. (David L. Ryan/The Boston Globe)
