   &QL; 
 &UR; PG&AMP;E _ &LR;  Pacific Gas and Electric Co. was handed one of its largest
rate increases ever yesterday when state regulators ended a year of
acrimonious debate by approving the most generous of three rival
funding proposals. By David Lazarus
</P>
<P>
   &UR; MICROSOFT  &LR; _ Downplaying reports that its newest system may be
infested with bugs, Microsoft yesterday launched Windows 2000 _ the
company's most ambitious software project ever _ with a curious mix
of tech-speak and celebrity pomp.
</P>
<P>
   Windows 2000, the business operating system that the Seattle
software giant itself calls a ``bet the ranch'' product, officially
became available through about 2,000 retail channels yesterday,
though it's already on the desktops of some 150,000 users,
including Microsoft's own 75,000 employees. By Kelly Zito
</P>
