Hiroshige. His prints, among the best that deal with popular
subject matter in the woodblock medium known as ukiyo-e (''the
floating world'') have had a lasting effect on Western art. Their
compositional innovations have reverberated in the works of
Impressionists and Post-Impressionists, notably Monet, van Gogh and
